<A>__{it's dark and stable in here, with just some creaks and intermittent vibrations. a poisonous green light spills from the other living room. coraline goes there, carrying the cat over her shoulder, past wallpaper that peels up as she passes, to the room where she last heard the sound of her mother's finger on glass.}
<L>__{interior other living room same}
<A>__{a poisonous green fire like sleepy sea snakes burns in the fireplace. the bug furniture looks grey now, their lights flickering as if short circuited; legs and wings twitching uncontrollably. coraline scans the walls, the ceiling, looking for a sign of her parents. angle on coraline in foreground. she senses the other mother behind her, a creature who is no sort of mother at all but a witch, a beldam. she turns. the beldam is hunched on the sofa her face hidden.}
